{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_bdrk_012YyAdULot6UXMpcEJJABBu","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"claude-opus-4-6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me update my progress and start implementing.\n\n`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`\n- **The problem:** Idea 3 is about using CMA-ES (Covariance Matrix Adaptation Evolution Strategy) to directly optimize StepML artifact parameters against BLIS E2E error, rather than per-step MAPE. This is a black-box optimization approach where BLIS is treated as a function mapping coefficients → E2E error.\n- **Key starting point:** Idea 1's trace replay achieved 56.2% mean E2E error (down from 427.8%). The error is *systematic under-prediction* — BLIS runs \"too fast.\" All experiments show ~50-63% E2E error. The overhead floor (step_overhead_us) appears to be the main knob.\n- **Parameter space is small:** Per model, we have ~8-15 parameters (regime coefficients, overhead, secondary methods). CMA-ES is well-suited for this dimensionality.\n`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1506,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5cda49b4-0eac-4d7d-a6da-e3880a46a823","uuid":"7cfd4647-c688-4ba7-9522-2551f29ef052"}
