{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_bdrk_013MPfyvjquymwp4DHpiamxo","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"claude-opus-4-6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`\n- **CMA-ES as DES calibrator:** This experiment demonstrates that derivative-free optimization (CMA-ES) can effectively calibrate discrete-event simulator parameters. The key insight: treat the simulator as a black-box function and optimize against end-to-end metrics directly, rather than per-component accuracy. This approach reduced E2E error from 56.2% → 15.1% across 10 experiments.\n- **The E2E ↔ ITL tradeoff:** The fundamental limitation discovered is that E2E = f(TTFT, ITL, scheduling) where f is nonlinear. Optimizing E2E alone allows the optimizer to sacrifice ITL (9.5% → 87.4%) to match total E2E. A Pareto-optimal approach would need multi-objective optimization (e.g., NSGA-II).\n- **Model-specific calibration is mandatory:** The per-model CMA-ES results vary dramatically (llama-2-70b: 8.3% vs mixtral: 25.9%). Each model's architecture (dense vs MoE), tensor parallelism, and resulting step-time distribution create fundamentally different calibration landscapes.\n`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`\n\nAll experiments are complete and documented. Here's the final summary:\n\n---\n\n## Idea 3: E2E Calibration — Complete\n\n### Sub-Hypothesis Results\n\n| # | Sub-Hypothesis | Status | Key Result |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| H1 | CMA-ES + trace replay | **PARTIALLY SUPPORTED** | **15.1%** mean E2E (target < 15%), **4/10 < 10%** |\n| H2 | Workload-spec mode | **NOT TESTED** | Infrastructure failure (profile file mismatch) |\n| H3 | Additive corrections | **REFUTED for E2E** | E2E +2.1pp worse; TTFT improved to **9.4%** |\n\n### Best Results Per Model\n\n| Model | Before (Idea 1) | After (CMA-ES) | Improvement |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| llama-2-7b | 60.9% | 22.2% | 2.7x |\n| llama-2-70b | 58.2% | **8.3%** | 7.0x |\n| mixtral-8x7b-v0-1 | 53.0% | 25.9% | 2.0x |\n| codellama-34b | 55.8% | **7.9%** | 7.1x |\n\n### Key Discovery\n**E2E and ITL are in fundamental tension** — optimizing one worsens the other. The LatencyModel interface's 5 methods interact nonlinearly through simulation dynamics. CMA-ES finds E2E-optimal coefficients that sacrifice per-token accuracy, producing 87.4% ITL error (up from 9.5%). Future work needs multi-objective optimization.\n\n### Artifacts Produced\n- 5 optimized StepML artifact JSONs (per model)\n- Go changes patch (32 lines: `--stepml-model` CLI flag)\n- Full per-experiment CSV results\n- CMA-ES convergence logs"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5cda49b4-0eac-4d7d-a6da-e3880a46a823","uuid":"3010aa1c-83f7-47c9-9b64-1cb7f272add6"}
